                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_fadyn_2" n="2" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fadyn</orth><form type="participle"><orth>fast</orth></form></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fadun</orth><form type="participle"><orth>fast</orth></form></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>покрываться сыпью</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>break out in a rash</q></abv:tr></sense><re><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fadynæg</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fadængæ</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>корь</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>measles</q></abv:tr></sense><sense xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>распускаться (о цветке)</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>blossom out</q></abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">в дигорском также</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">in Digor it also means</note></sense></re><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>jæ bwar rafasta</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>его тело покрылось сыпью</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>his body got covered with a rash</q></abv:tr></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Происхождение не ясно. Если допустить, что в основе лежит понятие „красноты“ (ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>cʼitela</w> <gloss><q>корь</q></gloss></mentioned> при <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>cʼiteli</w> <gloss><q>красный</q></gloss></mentioned>), то можно сблизить с <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>pāṭala-</w> <gloss><q>бледнокрасный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>paṭala-</w> <gloss><q>нанесенное краской пятно на теле</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">The origin is not clear. If one assumes that there is the concept of ‘redness’ in the stem (cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>cʼitela</w> <gloss><q>measles</q></gloss></mentioned> and <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>cʼiteli</w> <gloss><q>red</q></gloss></mentioned>), then it is possible to relate this word to <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>pāṭala-</w> <gloss><q>light red</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>paṭala-</w> <gloss><q>paint stain on a body</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>